Season
When the weather conditions remain the same for a long time, we call it 
season . Ther e are four main seasons in India.
Summer Season
Summer is the hot time of the year. This 
season lasts from April to June. The sun is 
very hot, in these mon ths. Days are long er 
and nigh ts are short er during this season. 
Hot winds called 'loo' blow in some areas. 
We use fans, cooler s and air conditioner s 
to keep ourselves cool. We like to wear 
cotton clothes in this season. 
Everybody enjo ys cold drink s and ice creams. People like to go to hill 
stations in summer s. Weather is pleasan t and cooler at hill stations. 
Mussorie, Kullu, Manali, Ooty are some hill stations.

Winter Season
The cold season is called the winter. 
December and Januar y are the cold 
mon ths. We wear woollen clothes. 
We use room heaters and 
some times mak e bonfires to keep 
ourselves w arm. W e ha ve hot f ood 
and hot drink s.
Spring Season
Itis the season that comes after  
winter and before summer . The 
trees get new leaves and flowers 
bloom in this season. This season 
is neither too hot nor too cold. The 
breeze becomes gentle and soft.
